      "content": "While choosing a peaceful fade might feel more poetic or less painful in the moment, suppressing the character's struggle could ironically rob them of a chance to truly live and mean something to the people who created that world. In many stories, a genuine end comes from making a final stand rather than fading before the struggle even truly begins, giving the character dignity and impact in their life. Please remember that your own feelings about fading are deeply real and deserve compassionate support from someone who can help you carry this emotional weight without losing yourself.",
